# Pokemon Battler — UI Fix Rules

## Tech Stack (DO NOT CHANGE)
- Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS + hand-written CSS in `apps/web/src/app/globals.css`
- Framer Motion for animations
- Space Grotesk + Inter fonts (already loaded via Google Fonts import in globals.css line 1)
- The web frontend is at `apps/web/`

## Critical Rules
- ❌ NEVER break existing functionality (battle system, wallet connection, Solana integration)
- ❌ NEVER change the file structure or add new frameworks/libraries
- ❌ NEVER remove existing components — only restyle them
- ❌ NEVER use placeholder images — the project already uses real Pokemon card images from `images.pokemontcg.io`
- ❌ NEVER change the battle engine, API routes, or backend packages
- ✅ ALWAYS preserve all existing class names and component props
- ✅ ALWAYS edit CSS in `apps/web/src/app/globals.css` (the single 2020-line CSS file)
- ✅ Only modify TSX files when the HTML structure needs changing for layout
- ✅ Keep all existing animations (Framer Motion in components + CSS keyframes in globals.css)
- ✅ When taking screenshots for comparison, use browser-tools MCP

## File Importance
- `globals.css` — 90% of UI changes go here (CSS vars, component styles)
- `page.tsx` — home page structure
- `NavBar.tsx` — navigation
- `TrendingCardScroll.tsx` — the Exebenus-style 3D card section (already exists, enhance only)
- `LoginHero.tsx` — login page hero
- `AppBackground.tsx` — background layer
